This paper deals with the construction of efficient data structures for answering distance queries in graphs subject to multiple vertex failures. This is a problem in graph algorithms and data structures, which is typically categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves techniques from computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT) for constructing the distance oracles. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of the distance oracles in network analysis and optimization, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
